In COVID Briefings, Trump Again Relies On Both Shock And Strategic RetreatEnlarge this image toggle caption Mandel Ngan/AFP via Getty Images Mandel Ngan/AFP via Getty ImagesPresident Trump's nightly briefings on COVID-19 this week have featured stunning pronouncements and reversals.
When questioned about more testing, Trump has repeatedly said that it was "up to the states."
The week was a crash course in the Trump style, issuing bold pronouncements, then dialing them back to seek another path.
On the night he declared his "total authority" over the states, Trump also said he would not need to use such powers.
If Congress won't officially adjourn, he said, he has "the power to adjourn Congress."